// Migrated from REST handlers in backend/internal/api/rest/v1/license*.go
// per .claude/plans/proto-naming-conventions.md. Conventions enforced:
//   * package proto.license.v1 + go_package suffix for dispatch
//   * service name = <Domain>Service, methods PascalCase verbs
//   * snake_case fields, no json_name annotations
//   * timestamps as string ISO-8601 (no google.protobuf.Timestamp)
//
// Auth model (conventions §3.5 EXCEPTION — system-wide, NOT org-scoped):
//   License is a deployment-wide configuration for OnPremise installations
//   — there is no per-org license, the whole server runs against ONE
//   active license at a time. Authentication splits into two surfaces:
//
//   1. `LicensePublicService` — unauthenticated. `GetStatus`, `GetLimits`,
//      `CheckFeature`. The login page hits these before any token exists
//      (the React app needs to know if the install is over-quota before
//      it can render the dashboard). Mirrors REST's `GET /api/v1/license/*`
//      which is also publicly accessible.
//
//   2. `LicenseService` — authenticated. `Activate`, `Upload`, `Refresh`,
//      `Validate`. REST gated these on `tenant.UserRole == "owner"` when
//      a tenant context existed (i.e., the request flowed through the
//      org-scoped middleware). Connect handlers re-create that policy by
//      checking the caller's tenant context — when present, role must be
//      owner; when absent (initial OnPremise activation before any org
//      exists), the auth interceptor enforces a valid JWT and that is the
//      bar to clear.
//
// Wire-shape parity:
//   The REST surface returned `billing.LicenseStatus` from /status; the
//   proto `LicenseStatus` message mirrors that struct field-for-field.
//   GetLimits returned `{limits: {...}, plan: ...}` on REST — the proto
//   `LicenseLimitsResponse` keeps both fields at top level (limits + plan).
//   ActivateLicense + ValidateLicense returned a 200 envelope `{message,
//   status}` and `{valid, license_key, ...}` respectively; both proto
//   messages return the entity directly (`LicenseStatus` for activate /
//   refresh / upload, `ValidatedLicense` for validate) per conventions §9.

